<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home1.stofanet.dk/remmer/mitigation.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
So, the closer you get the top of the bell-curve to 1, the less value of any further AC/ID.<br>
<br>
Perhaps parses of &quot;Ideal&quot; (per mob, naturally), or the point of lower return AC (with the top at 1) should be parsed with the emphasis on numbers 2-19 hit instead of average damage. When the bell-curve top hits 1-2, then 100AC more added will get lower yield than the previous 100AC added. <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370955 target=blank>Sage Aauminki Iceblade</a><br><a href=http://www.vazaelle.dk target=blank>Caer Cadarn</a></big><br>Vazaelle Server</center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aauminki>Aauminki</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/5/03 12:11:13 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lythe@thesteelwarrior>Lythe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/6/03 3:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3094.topic&index=63>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Mitigation coefficient</span><hr size=1> I'm sure most of you know this,  but I don't see anyone here talking in terms of a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>mitigation coefficient</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, which one would define as: <br>
<br>
mitCoeff = (Avg - min) / (Max - min)<br>
<br>
(Or any equivalent scaled or re-scaled definition using damage intervals etc..).  This particular definition scales as :<br>
mitCoeff -&gt; 0 as AC -&gt; infinity (Min hit every time).  mitCoeff -&gt; 1 if class = monk (haha), the &quot;No AC&quot; max every time regime <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
If you consider tests in terms of this kind of universal scaling quantity, not only do you have a meaningful way to talk about tests on different mobs with different DB/DI (if their atk and your ac are the same,  should give same mitCoeff).  You also have a meaningful way to talk about the actual % change in mitigation.<br>
<br>
<br>
Lythe<br>
<br>
