<br>
Lets take a hypotethical mob that quads, max hit for 2000 and that max hits 20% of the time. Now, lets say you have 8000 hp and the mob hits you on every hit, ignoring evasion.<br>
<br>
1 in  625 quad rounds, you will die instantly, where heals wont matter(2000+2000+2000+2000=8000).<br>
<br>
Now, Lets say he hits for max 10% of the time.<br>
<br>
Now, you will have this incident 1 in 10000(0.1*0.1*0.1*0.1) quads. But still, the average damage wouldnt be more than maybe 10% lower.<br>
<br>
So, the more often you get hit for max damage, the higher chance it is for spikes in damage(growing exponentially). Spikes in damage are what very often kills the MT.<br>
<br>
I might do a check on some logs and do a sliding window over each 5 hits a mob does and see how different AC values changes spike occurences.<br>
