<br>
I did 2 tests. 1 with 746 AC(25.7% for max hit) and other with 1315 AC(5.7% for max hit) .<br>
<br>
Results with 10 hits in a row with over 1150 damage(max is 1490):<br>
746ac: 1234 sequences  from 8096 hits &gt; 1150 (1 in 6.56 sequences)<br>
1315ac: 5 sequences  from 7655 hits &gt; 1150 (1 in 1531 sequences)<br>
<br>
<br>
With 746ac the highest 10 sequence were 1411.<br>
With 1315ac the highest 10 sequence were 1187<br>
<br>
This were just to show that spikes grows exponentially with lower ac, while the average damage is more linear. Ofcourse, the spikes arent exponentially more damage, but lets say a mob hits you quickly 10 times and you have 1150 hp, you will die ALOT more from having 746 ac than 1315 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fatsow99>Fatsow99</A> at: 4/8/03 5:28:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eldryc>Eldryc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 145<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/8/03 9:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3094.topic&index=73>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC</span><hr size=1> The dmg spikes is why I've always questioned the uber mob tanking thread where it's suggested that warriors use evasive if the DI/DB is less than 0.13.  Okay, I'll take less overall dmg if I use evasive on those mobs, but what about spikes?  It's the spikes that usually kill me if I'm the main tank.  Unless the mob has ridiculously high DB and very low DI, the contribution of Defensive discipline to reducing those spikes will be quite significant.  Evasive will make a spike less likely, but a max hit spike could still happen.  Defensive makes that impossible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http:/